{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d42eb861-9ad3-4e6b-99b8-b0988c63c0d6","content":"No files found in the working directory, so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is the addition of:\n```\nxmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\nx:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n## Catching binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are validated by the XAML compiler (`XamlC`). To ensure errors surface at build time:\n\n**1. Confirm XamlC is enabled** (it's on by default in .NET MAUI, but you can be explicit in your `.csproj`):\n\n```xml\n<MauiXamlCCompilation>true</MauiXamlCCompilation>\n```\n\n**2. What gets caught at build time:**\n- Misspelled property names (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) → **compiler error**\n- Wrong property types (e.g., binding a `string` to `IsToggled`) → **compiler error**\n- Missing properties on the ViewModel → **compiler error**\n\n**3. If you need to opt out for a subtree** (e.g., dynamically-typed context), use:\n```xml\n<StackLayout x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\">\n    <!-- falls back to reflection-based binding -->\n</StackLayout>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` can be set on any element and is inherited by children.\n- Compiled bindings are also **faster** (no runtime reflection).\n- If your ViewModel is in another assembly, use the full `clr-namespace:...;assembly=...` syntax.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"21a615f4-7e90-4932-8294-7a51eb698fe7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking me to help them convert a hypothetical SettingsPage.xaml to use compiled bindings. Since there are no files, I'll provide the guidance directly with code examples.","outputTokens":772,"requestId":"77C3:E2933:7D79539:8BA253C:69EABD86"},"id":"411c973a-2d39-4275-9cdb-ede2eaec5632","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:47:19.343Z","parentId":"f2d907ab-7cca-4098-940c-82c90c6eef47"}
